article.description: Jordan Jackson had 22 points as Texas Rio Grande Valley romped past Division II-member Texas A&M-International 79-52 on Monday night.
article.headline: Jackson’s 22 PTs leads UTRGV past Texas A&M-International
article.linkText: Jackson’s 22 PTs leads UTRGV past Texas A&M-International
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Jordan Jackson had 22 points as Texas Rio Grande Valley romped past Division II-member Texas A&M-International 79-52 on Monday night. Quinton Johnson II had 11 points for Texas Rio Grande Valley (2-4). Lesley Varner II added 10 points. Matija Novkovic had 13 points for the Dustdevils. Jorge Mejias-Sanchez added six assists. Caleb Highley had seven rebounds. Texas Rio Grande Valley takes on Texas A&M-Corpus Christi at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
